Bias: Biased towards one class ( major data on either of dog or cat )
So if we show a cat image the model might predict it as Dog

Variance : range of data
Eg: Salaries majorly uotp 5 lakhs , and some with 10+ lakhas and few with 20+ and very few with 30+

Best model: Low bias and low variance
Bias variance trade off , we need to maintain low bias and variance so model doesnt get over fit

When we use regression models to train data , the model will overfit , to overcome this we use Regularization
Here in linear equation we do not want huge weights/coeffs

-> Lasso : penalizses where there are weights , we introduce lambda
-> Ridge: Penalize more in strict way 

ridge sherinks coeffs to almost zero , but never 0.
We use lasso for feature selection

-> Elastic net : combo of lasso and ridge



Why Regularization? 
To reduce variance of model , without substantial increase in bias.




